  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope — patient-specific VAD implant decisions in adult heart-failure populations, operating range 3–6 L/min at 2000–3500 RPM — is described in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed; all 13 credibility factors are assessed. Decision: Accepted.",
