      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to the clinical endpoint stated in the device submission requirement.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is NIH (g/100 L), which is the metric specified in the device submission requirement for Class III VAD safety evaluation. Direct clinical relevance confirmed at gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
