    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed and each achieved level meets or exceeds the required level for Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms the 95th-percentile NIH prediction remains within the clinically acceptable threshold. The computational model is deemed credible for predicting absolute hemolysis levels for the Class III VAD device across the operating envelope described in the bound Requirement and Claim. Decision: Accepted.",
